9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 751, L.D. 1146, “An Act Regarding the
10 Required State of Mind Relating to Robbery”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in paragraph B in the 2nd line (page 1, line 5 in L.D.) by
12 striking out the following: "intentionally or knowingly" and inserting the following:
13 'intentionally or knowingly'
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, updates the existing
1188 robbery statute's mens rea requirement for the act of threatening to use force to clarify that
1199 the act must be done intentionally or knowingly in order for the actor to have a culpable
2200 state of mind to be found criminally liable of robbery.
